deck_description: Deck focused in destruction and reborn to gain effects

Hi there, this is Macuii, first time uploading a deck; anyway, let gets stated:

Been a fan of Lightsworns since Dragon Rulers, but since they got banned I've been looking for a way to make this archetype better in this current format.

This deck consist mainly of Lightsworn, Dangers, Chaos, and some Supports. Also I have included the Baroness of de Fleur (OCG, eventually TCG).

I feel that what makes this deck different from other Chaos Lightsworn is that I have included Puzzlomino, which can give you the opportunity to summon a variety of Synchros of different levels. For this deck it helped me to summon Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon.

As for my Extras Deck, is the generic Number XYZ, Synchro, and Links you will find in this type of deck.

For the Side Deck: I have include more replacement for Extra Monsters. (No hand traps since they are gonna end up milled into the graveyard)

No pro here, so, you are more than welcome to edit this recipe as you like. Hopefully this will bring the Chaos Lightsworn back in game.

Constructive opinions , and recommendations are very welcomed. Enjoy!!!

deck_name: Kings of Different Dimension: Reiji Akaba Deck,D/D/D Marksma
deck_description: https://youtu.be/bf1knmdPtj0

This is pretty much a standard VW deck with the addition of a special summon lock with Fossil Dyna.

The target end board:

Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon, Ultimaya, Beatice, Dragonlark, Fossil Dyna (summoned on opponent Standby Phase from Dragonlark), Chuche

It's pretty easy to pull off consistently and if you get hand trapped, you can always default back to Crystal Wing + Shenshen + Chuche or Crystal Wing + Caliga + Chuche.

The 2x Effect Veiler and 2x TTT can be replaced with Psy-frame Gear Gamma and Driver. If you go this route you can add in Vahram, the Magistus Divinity Dragon to make with gamma and driver on your turn and pop Vahram with Chuche to destroy all face up cards your opponent controls.

Tip #1: If Fossil Dyna or Caliga are on your field next turn and you need to activate monster effects or special summon, you can use Qinglong to negate Dyna or Caliga and continue playing.

Tip #2: You can use a Chuche in the GY to level Shenshen to 12 and overlay with Ultimaya Tzolkin to hard make Divine Arsenal AA Zeus.

Inspired by Yacine656's VW list.

deck_excerpt: Set up your Pendulum Scales and spam monsters
deck_description:
A somewhat free-form deck that's highly customizable and pretty flexible. There are a ton of gimmicks you can mix and match. This is just one of many paths you could take.

Use GrandSolfachord Musecia, DoSolfachord Cutia, Solfachord Elegance, Diviner of the Heralds and or Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm to search the pendulum scales you need, then Pendulum Summon and toolbox. Almost always at minimum your opponent can't negate the pendulum summon (so no Solemns), and usually your opponent can't activate effects (so no Ash, Veiler, Imperm as long as you pendulum summon at least 1 Solfachord).

Crusadia Equimax into Magius + a Special Summon (Angelia, Dreamia, Supreme King Gate Zero, sometimes Trias Hierarchia, even DoSolfachord Coolia) searches a Tuner that summons itself.

Gate Zero can also become a Tuner to access Halqifibrax with it's on-field effect. Pop a scale to summon Shooting Riser Dragon from your Extra Deck, then Gate Zero puts itself into the scale, replacing the card you just popped.

Remember that Ash and Veiler are also Tuners. You can use Veiler + Trias to summon Baroness, or Ash + Gracia to summon Savage Dragon off of Halq, or just Pendulum Summon them if the situation calls for it.

Cross-Sheep can pull a Tuner like Diviner out of the GY for Synchro or Halq plays (or any monster really for whatever you want) when combo'd with Odd-Eyes Absolute Dragon.

Verte Anaconda is an easy monster you can summon with even the worst hands and summons basically Kirin 2.0 for free lol this card's mega broken

In simpler gamestates and versus some decks the Solfachords' battle and protection effects really shine. Don't forget that the field spell has a pop effect if you control 3 even-scaled (2, 4, 6, 8) or 3 odd-scaled (1, 3, 5, 7) which even lets you beat things like Mystic Mine. Might play more than 1 copy since a smart opponent will likely aim all their removal at it.

And of course the monsters are cute!

deck_excerpt: A Drytron deck that is anything but Drytron just doing Drytron things...
deck_description: Deck test video link is down below https://youtube.com/watch?v=Nly23sUbuCE&feature=youtu.be   What makes me so fascinated about Drytrons is how they can turn a very archaic summoning mechanic into a fresh, polished Nokia phone. However, what makes them stand out from most of the compulsive decks that had been put in the spotlight is the ease of getting it's resources; alongside with building boards while recycling monsters that synchronize each other (not related to synchro summoning). In such cases, It can (within one turn) can allow itself to Apollousa at its based 3200ATK. Drytron also can easily open foward with the Dragoon Turbo (if Verte could go 5 minutes without the negations, which doesn't matter for the most part as Dragoon Turbo is just a 2 way intersection). Now the twist is I added in some interesting tech options that have it's fair share of benefits A new card going by the name "Ready Fusion" is a new spell card that shares its conditions with the infamous "Instant Fusion" (tl;dr pay 1000LP to Special Summon level 6 or lower fusion Monster). Sadly the deal breaker for the new card is the fact that the only Fusions Monsters allowed to be summoned are Vanilla monsters. Luckily, I have two on my disposal which can be used to Synchro Summon "Chaos Ruler the Chaotic Magical Dragon" if needed; or for them to be used to aid extendors like "Diviner of the Herald", and "Beatrice, Lady of the Eternal". Another very particular card I used in this deck also happens to be a once niche tech option in ritual decks long ago. "Magician of Black Chaos MAX" is a ritual monster to be summoned with either the spell card "Chaos Form" (if the Dragoon Turbo was done successfully), or can be used with Drytron's Ritual Spell "Meteonis Drytron" (a much easier option). Now what makes my reason of choice to add it in is due to the effects of shutting down Opponents Monster Effects for the turn; and also the ability to add a spell card from the GY to the hand (of any choice), after a monster is destroyed by battle (not the best effect in the world, but one that comes in handy when you need certain Spell Cards like TTT, Drytron Nova, and Called by the Grave). Monster Reborn I added in there to recover monsters for further play extensions or to regain monsters like "Magician of Black Chaos MAX". Forgot to mention that Zeus fits comfortably right in with the XYZ monsters within the deck as well :)

deck_excerpt: The power of Gladiator Beasts unites with the Mekk-Knight engine!
deck_description: A fun idea which works pretty well online for a Gladiator Beast deck. I came up with the idea at the same time that I was learning about Mekk-Knights and then I saw a deck on yugioh-card which had a few Mekk-Knights in it, and thought I should try the Mekk-Knight engine here. World Legacy's Secret is a pretty good card that can also be used to recycle Gladiator Beast Tamer Editor, other than providing monster negates when you have a Mekk-Knight. The Mekk-Knight engine also helps with the age-old problem of Ashing a Rescue Rabbit or a Test Panther and stopping you in your tracks. Aside from that, it provides access to Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy and Dingirsu, the Orcust of the Evening Star. Yes, I know that not everyone is comfortable playing about 40 cards, but I've gotten used to running Glads at 45 cards. This is a deck that I want to try in real life, the only cards that I don't have yet are Mekk-Knight Blue Sky and Mekk-Knight Purple Nightfall.

deck_excerpt: Link Apple Engine > Foolish Burial Goods Engine
deck_description:
Removed Allure & Acquisitiveness. Things to remember:
  • You can't use Link Apple after Pot of Duality on the same turn.
  • Don't accidentally kill yourself with Multiple Destruction.
Consider playing:
  • Cynet Mining & Flame Bufferlo to turn Cyberses in hand into draws.
  • Draw of Fate to close the duel quicker.

Deck is built to mainly go second but can handle going first if you can get Mechaba, Hope Harbinger with a Strike on set on bored first turn there is no reason why you should be losing those games.

Side note this is just the v1 build of the deck as I understand it and play with it more I will be making the changes needed, upstart can be changed to whatever you like just don't play pot of desires banishing 10 cards to draw 2 in this deck is a neg 8 also you can lose key cards that make this deck run. DO NOT play 3 blue-eyes unless you decide to play "Mausoleum of White" over "Magical Meltdown" which then you could play 3 blue eyes so you can get more value out of Mausoleum but then your forced to play "Maiden With Eyes of Blue" which you don't really need in a Invoked build of Blue Eyes because you have "Crystron Halqifibrax" in the extra deck.

I am considering playing "Swing of Memories" in the main and "Ghost of a Grudge" in the side deck as ghost is good for going for easy otk's as it doesn't target it's good for getting rid of problematic monsters on the bored.
